modules.description: This module provides functions to compress and decompress data streams using the Camlzip library. It operates on input and output stream types (`Iostream.In`, `Iostream.Out`, and their buffered variants), allowing for on-the-fly compression and decompression of byte streams. Concrete use cases include reading from or writing to compressed files, network communication with compressed data, and processing compressed archives without needing to store the entire data in memory.
